  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "To get change for a new 2000 INR note, you can consider the following options:\n\n1. **Banks**: Visit a nearby bank branch; they can provide change for larger denominations.\n\n2. **ATMs**: Some ATMs dispense smaller denomination notes. If you withdraw an amount less than 2000 INR, you may receive change.\n\n3. **Local Shops or Businesses**: Retailers, grocery stores, or restaurants might be able to provide change. Purchasing a small item can help facilitate this.\n\n4. **Friends and Family**: Ask someone you know if they can provide change for your note.\n\n5. **Marketplaces or Street Vendors**: Vendors are often accustomed to handling various denominations and may be able to provide change.\n\nEnsure that the note is in good condition, as damaged notes might create issues when trying to get change.",
